{"id": "EUVD-2023-57428", "enisaUuid": "7b2bdd0e-b21d-3dcd-a9cb-a986966a520f", "description": "A bug in QEMU could cause a guest I/O operation otherwise addressed to an arbitrary disk offset to be targeted to offset 0 instead (potentially overwriting the VM's boot code). This could be used, for example, by L2 guests with a virtual disk (vdiskL2) stored on a virtual disk of an L1 (vdiskL1) hypervisor to read and/or write data to LBA 0 of vdiskL1, potentially gaining control of L1 at its next reboot.", "datePublished": "2023-11-03T13:58:50", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-06T22:57:21", "baseScore": 6.4, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2023-5088", "https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=2247283", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2024/03/msg00012.html", "https://lore.kernel.org/all/20230921160712.99521-1-simon.rowe@nutanix.com/T/", "https://security.netapp.com/advisory/ntap-20231208-0005/", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2024:2135", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2024:2962", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-5088", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/04/msg00042.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-5088"], "assigner": "redhat", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0b7d4d1a-4d4a-3b88-a472-6f72d7c5f224", "product": {"name": "Red Hat Enterprise Linux 9"}, "product_version": "patch: 17:8.2.0-11.el9_4"}, {"id": "67913712-8fbe-32ee-9714-92e89e00d9c1", "product": {"name": "Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8"}, "product_version": "patch: 8100020240314161907.e155f54d"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "5e711926-7e94-36b2-ba96-d59a973ff224", "vendor": {"name": "Red Hat"}}], "isExploited": false}